CASH

FLOW FROM OPERATIONS INCREASED $3.4 BILLION DUE TO AN INCREASE IN CASH RECEIVED FROM CUSTOMERS DRIVEN BY 15% REVENUE GROWTH, ALONG WITH A $1.6 BILLION DECREASE IN CASH OUTFLOW FOR OTHER CURRENT ASSETS PRIMARILY REFLECTING CHANGES IN INVENTORY. CASH

