, WHICH REQUIRES ADDITIONAL DISCLOSURES ABOUT THE OBJECTIVES OF DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND HEDGING ACTIVITIES, THE METHOD OF ACCOUNTING FOR THOSE INSTRUMENTS UNDER SFAS NO. 133 AND ITS RELATED

INTERPRETATIONS, AND A TABULAR DISCLOSURE OF THE EFFECTS OF THOSE INSTRUMENTS AND RELATED HEDGED ITEMS ON OUR FINANCIAL POSITION, FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE, AND CASH FLOWS. SFAS NO. 161 IS EFFECTIVE FOR US BEGINNING JANUARY 1, 2009. WE ARE

