PROPERTY AND EQUIPMENT ARE STATED AT COST. DEPRECIATION IS COMPUTED PRINCIPALLY ON THE STRAIGHT-LINE METHOD

OVER THE ESTIMATED USEFUL LIVES OF THE ASSETS. THE USEFUL LIVES FOR BUILDINGS RANGE FROM FIVE TO 15 YEARS, LEASEHOLD IMPROVEMENTS GENERALLY RANGE FROM TWO TO TEN YEARS  REPRESENTING THE APPLICABLE LEASE TERMS PLUS REASONABLY ASSURED

EXTENSIONS, COMPUTER EQUIPMENT AND SOFTWARE RANGE FROM TWO TO THREE YEARS, AND FURNITURE AND EQUIPMENT RANGE FROM ONE TO FIVE YEARS. LAND IS NOT DEPRECIATED.

