AS A RESULT OF THE FAST ACQUISITION, WE RECORDED $981 MILLION OF GOODWILL IN OUR MICROSOFT BUSINESS DIVISION. OF THE $266 MILLION OF ACQUIRED INTANGIBLE ASSETS, $35 MILLION WAS ASSIGNED TO IN-PROCESS RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT ASSETS AND WAS

EXPENSED. THE REMAINING ACQUIRED INTANGIBLE ASSETS INCLUDE $27 MILLION OF CUSTOMER RELATIONSHIPS WITH A WEIGHTED AVERAGE LIFE OF SEVEN YEARS, $134 MILLION OF TECHNOLOGY-BASED INTANGIBLE ASSETS WITH A WEIGHTED AVERAGE LIFE OF FIVE YEARS, AND $70

MILLION OF OTHER INTANGIBLE ASSETS WITH A WEIGHTED AVERAGE LIFE OF SIX YEARS.

