DURING FISCAL YEAR 2008, WE REACHED A SETTLEMENT WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) ON ITS

2000-2003 EXAMINATION. AS A RESULT, WE REDUCED OUR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS BY $4.8 BILLION AND RECOGNIZED A TAX PROVISION REDUCTION OF $1.2 BILLION. WE ARE UNDER AUDIT BY THE IRS FOR THE TAX YEARS 2004-2006. WE DO NOT BELIEVE IT IS

REASONABLY POSSIBLE THAT THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS WILL SIGNIFICANTLY INCREASE OR DECREASE WITHIN THE NEXT 12 MONTHS AS WE DO NOT BELIEVE THE EXAMINATION WILL BE CONCLUDED WITHIN THE NEXT 12 MONTHS. AS A RESULT OF OUR SETTLEMENT

